Ecoblitz Flowering Phenology

Alec Brooks

2024-05-22

Statistics

The Phenology dataset is 11 variables gathered over 183 observations. the variables are stored mostly as character types, with a few doubles used for year and phenology status. there are no NAs or missing values within the dataset.

The variables of interest are Only Buds, Early, Peak, Late, Only Fruits. other useful variables for context and filtering are Year, season, Transect, Family, Species, and Common Name. Although the variables of interest are stored as doubles they appear to be boolean.

The total observations differ by year.

table(Flr$Year)
## 
## 2021 2022 2023 
##   49   72   62

and by season.

summary_tables <- list()
# 2021
Flr2 <- filter(Flr, Flr$Year==2021)
summary_tables[[1]] <- table(Flr2$season)
# 2022
Flr2 <- filter(Flr, Flr$Year==2022)
summary_tables[[2]] <- table(Flr2$season)
# 2023
Flr2 <- filter(Flr, Flr$Year==2023)
summary_tables[[3]] <- table(Flr2$season)
# sum
summary_table <- do.call(rbind, summary_tables)
rownames(summary_table) <- c("2021", "2022","2023")
summary_table
##      Fall Spring
## 2021   21     28
## 2022   17     55
## 2023   22     40

Family Plots by season and year

2021

List of families not present in both fall and spring.

Spring_data <- filter(Flr, Year == 2021 & season == "Spring")
Fall_data <- filter(Flr, Year == 2021 & season == "Fall")
Spring_Family <- unique(Spring_data$Family)
Fall_Family <- unique(Fall_data$Family)
Family_only_in_spring <- setdiff(Spring_Family, Fall_Family)
Family_only_in_fall <- setdiff(Fall_Family, Spring_Family)
Family_not_in_both <- union(Family_only_in_spring, Family_only_in_fall)
print(Family_not_in_both)
##  [1] "Ephedraceae"      "Lamiaceae"        "Polygonaceae"     "Boraginaceae"

## [13] "Typhaceae"        "Vitaceae"
